# .sanitize-patterns.example — copy to .sanitize-patterns (gitignored)
# and replace placeholders with your real personal identifiers.
#
# scripts/sanitize-check.sh reads this file line-by-line and fails the
# pre-commit hook if any tracked file matches a non-comment line.
#
# One ERE pattern per line. Empty lines and # comments are ignored.
# Plain literals work — they don't have to be valid regex if they
# contain no regex metacharacters. Escape dots in IPs (\.).
#
# Examples (REPLACE before use):
#
# your-real-name
# 192\.168\.42
# /home/operator-username
# /mnt/personal-mount
# personal-email-prefix
# yourdomain\.com
